dc_description_s: Project: ST-70|Scale: 1:2400|Drainage basin: Delaware River|Image is from a copy of the original on Mylar.|Drawn by J.W. Moses|Date October 1936 Approved|All bearings referred to N.J. Grid Bearing established by U.S. Coast & Geodetic Survey. Co-ordinates referred to same origin. Levels referred to Local Control Survey Datum. Origin of Latitude 38 degrees-50N. Longitude 74 degrees-40W. Coordiate X-2000 000.00' Y=0.00' (Mercater Projection) Creek stationing taken along north creek bank.|This survey has been projected from U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey Triangulation station at Mt. Holly with on an Azimuth of 289 degrees 51'-31.9" to water tower at Pemberton. Coordinate of Mt. Holly being taken as X 1965798.70-Y.425843.30. To refer elevations at this map to U.S.E.D datum ADD 7.901 wherever the words U.S.C.8G Survey is used it is intended to mean the local control system for the state of N.J.
